<p>
    Beginning with the 2015-2016, NBA TV Production will be using a new method of changing routes to TOC when transitioning from a show in one control room to
    the other. The 3 control rooms that are part of this new workflow are PCR 21, PCR 24, and PCR 12.
</p>
<p>
    In this new format, the external aux router in PCR 21 (on the bottom of the router stack to the left of the TD) will be the router used to swap routes to
    TOC.
    <strong>
        What this means (and this can’t be emphasized enough), is that the switcher in PCR 21 is now the cross point to TOC. The PCR 21 switcher MUST remain
        online and active when shows are being sent to TOC from either PCR 24 or PCR 12 (and of course, PCR 21). Do not restart this switcher under any
        circumstances while shows are going on in PCR 24 or PCR 12 as it will kill the transmission to TOC.
    </strong>
</p>
<p>
    In order to accommodate this new setup, the outputs of PCR 24 and PCR 12 are routed into the preselect router in PCR 21. It’s important to note that for
    each control room, we are taking <strong>output 2</strong> into the preselect router. This is done in order to accommodate the embedded audio which is part
    of output 2 from each room.
</p>
<p>
    In the current setup, we are using preselects 82-84. The routes on the preselect router in PCR 21 look like this (note that HD BARS are also routed to
    PSL-68; this will be covered below):
</p>
